* SOME INFORMATION ON AUGMENTA.MAC MACROS
	1) /FontPath= filespec tells @AUGMENTA.HLP^CHANGE_FONT[Change_Font] where to look for font files.
To use the Change_Font macro, you must create a RAM-resident copy of the
SAVE_PTR table and set the text and or/graphics mode auxiliary font area
pointers. EGA_FNT.ASM and VGA_FNT.ASM are sample programs that perform the
task.

	2) Port_IO macro allows you to read from / write to 80x86 I/O ports.
Input:
	Return_Str should contain hexadecimal port number;
	Return_Int = value to send to port (for OUTB or OUTW commands).
	Macro command line must be one of the commands: INB, INW, OUTB, OUTW.
Output:
	Return_Str = '' -- no error, otherwise Return_Str = error message;
	Return_Int = value read from port (for INB or INW commands).

	3) The macro Call_Far lets you make a call to FAR routine somewhere
	in memory.
Input:
	Return_Int = 32 bit address (segment:offset) of far routine.

	4) The macro ACCENTS (assigned to <CNTR>) provides a means of
inputting international without the need to use an international keyboard
driver. When the cursor is under, or to the right of, the letter over which
you desire to place an accent, hit <CNTR> (i.e. <5> on numeric keypad) and
then the desired accent (', `, ^, ~, etc.). Alternatively, you can hit the
